WEBVTT

00:00.331 --> 00:04.181
[ AL GREEN'S
"LET'S STAY TOGETHER" PLAYS ]

00:09.430 --> 00:11.180
GOOD MORNING, KADY.
HOW'S DADDY'S LITTLE APPLE HEAD?

00:11.182 --> 00:13.182
FINE.

00:13.184 --> 00:15.604
AH, THANK YOU.

00:15.596 --> 00:17.096
FOR WHAT?

00:17.098 --> 00:19.018
OH, THERE'S NO MORE OF THAT?
COULD YOU MAKE ME A CUP?

00:19.019 --> 00:21.059
NO, I AM NOT YOUR MAID.

00:21.062 --> 00:22.732
I AM HER NANNY.

00:22.733 --> 00:24.653
¿VERDAD, MI AMORCITA?

00:24.645 --> 00:26.605
I DON'T WANT THIS ANYMORE.

00:26.607 --> 00:28.237
IT'S OKAY, BABY,
JUST THROW IT ON THE FLOOR.

00:28.239 --> 00:29.569
THE NANNY WILL GET IT.

00:29.570 --> 00:31.450
[ SPEAKING SPANISH ]

00:31.452 --> 00:33.492
[ IMITATES NANNY ]

00:33.494 --> 00:36.504
MORNING, EVERYBODY.

00:36.497 --> 00:38.157
HEY, BABY,
DRINK YOUR JUICE, OKAY?

00:38.159 --> 00:39.959
OKAY, MOMMY.
THAT'S MY GIRL.

00:39.960 --> 00:41.330
OH, MY GOD, LOOK AT THE TIME.
I'M LATE AGAIN.

00:41.332 --> 00:43.542
THAT'S 'CAUSE YOU'RE
DOING TOO MUCH.

00:43.544 --> 00:45.764
YOU NEED
TO SLOW DOWN.

00:45.756 --> 00:47.126
I CAN'T.
I HAVE A BREAKFAST MEETING

00:47.128 --> 00:48.758
WITH A POTENTIAL CLIENT.

00:48.759 --> 00:50.129
THIS GUY DOES A LOT
OF ONLINE TRADING,

00:50.131 --> 00:51.841
AND I THINK
I'M GOING TO GET HIM.

00:51.842 --> 00:53.222
HEY, WAIT A MINUTE.

00:53.224 --> 00:55.064
LET'S HAVE BREAKFAST
TOGETHER AS A FAMILY.

00:55.055 --> 00:56.635
REMEMBER HOW WE USED
TO TURN THE MUSIC ON,

00:56.637 --> 00:58.977
EVERYBODY WOULD BE DANCING,
AND LAUGHING, AND FIGHTING --

00:58.979 --> 01:00.479
I MISS THAT.

01:00.481 --> 01:02.231
SO DO I, BUT...

01:02.233 --> 01:04.113
I ONLY HAVE TIME
FOR A CUP OF COFFEE.

01:04.105 --> 01:05.525
OH! I'LL GET IT FOR YOU.

01:05.525 --> 01:07.146
OH, THANK YOU, ROSA.

01:09.029 --> 01:10.449
HEY, JANET.

01:10.451 --> 01:12.071
YEAH.

01:12.072 --> 01:13.452
I GOT AN IDEA.
WHY DON'T WE

01:13.454 --> 01:15.124
TAKE THE DAY OFF AND HAVE
BREAKFAST TOGETHER IN BED?

01:15.116 --> 01:17.246
I'LL COOK.

01:17.248 --> 01:19.748
WHAT DO I HAVE TO DO TO GET YOU
TO TAKE MY JOB MORE SERIOUSLY?

01:19.750 --> 01:21.160
UH, QUIT IT?

01:21.162 --> 01:23.202
GET AWAY.

01:23.204 --> 01:25.844
COME ON, JAY,
THIS WAS SUPPOSED TO BE

01:25.836 --> 01:27.206
A LITTLE PART-TIME JOB.

01:27.208 --> 01:29.798
YEAH, WELL, IT IS,
BUT I GOT TO WORK LATE.

01:29.800 --> 01:31.170
OH, AND, MICHAEL, I NEED YOU
TO BE MY SWEETIE

01:31.172 --> 01:32.712
AND COOK DINNER TONIGHT.

01:32.713 --> 01:34.093
BUT I WAS YOUR SWEETIE
LAST NIGHT,

01:34.094 --> 01:37.724
AND THE NIGHT BEFORE, I WAS
THE BIG CHOCOLATE GUMMY BEAR.

01:37.718 --> 01:39.718
HA HA HA!

01:39.720 --> 01:42.220
PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE...

01:42.223 --> 01:44.613
OKAY, I'LL NUKE
SOME CHICKEN.

01:44.605 --> 01:46.275
THANK YOU.

01:46.277 --> 01:48.277
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT? I REALLY
MISS WATCHING YOU COOK, JAY.

01:48.279 --> 01:50.609
THE WAY YOU USED TO DO THAT
THING WITH THE MIXING BOWL --

01:50.611 --> 01:52.151
WHAT THING?

01:52.153 --> 01:53.533
THE THING YOU DO.

01:53.534 --> 01:56.004
Kady: HA HA!

01:55.996 --> 01:57.366
HERE YOU GO, JAY.

01:57.368 --> 01:58.998
THANK YOU, ROSA.

01:58.999 --> 02:01.159
I'M HAPPY
TO DO IT FOR YOU.

02:01.162 --> 02:03.792
LET'S GO OUTSIDE
AND PLAY.

02:03.794 --> 02:05.174
Janet:
BYE-BYE, HONEY.

02:05.166 --> 02:06.796
BYE-BYE.

02:06.797 --> 02:08.957
BYE, BABY.
KICK THE HORSIE. KICK IT.

02:10.170 --> 02:11.591
THAT WOMAN HATES ME.

02:11.592 --> 02:13.092
MICHAEL...

02:18.389 --> 02:19.639
YO, MOM.

02:19.640 --> 02:21.060
YO, JUNIOR, WHASSUP?

02:21.061 --> 02:22.221
I WAS WONDERING --

02:22.223 --> 02:24.573
NO!
YOU DIDN'T LET ME FINISH.

02:24.565 --> 02:27.435
I'M SORRY, SON, WHAT IS IT?
WHAT DO YOU NEED? WHAT, WHAT?

02:27.438 --> 02:29.728
CAN I HAVE $35 TO GO TO
A RAP CONCERT SATURDAY NIGHT?

02:29.730 --> 02:31.980
NO!
OH, COME ON, MOM.

02:31.982 --> 02:33.982
HEY, YOU WANT TO APPEAL
MY DECISION?

02:33.984 --> 02:36.374
TAKE IT TO THE HIGHER COURT.
BYE, JUNIOR.

02:36.367 --> 02:37.487
YO, DAD, WHASSUP?

02:37.488 --> 02:39.198
GOOD MORNING, SON.

02:39.200 --> 02:42.120
MOM SAID TO GIVE ME $35
SO I CAN GO TO A RAP CONCERT.

02:42.122 --> 02:44.342
IS THAT WHAT SHE SAID
OR ARE YOU PARAPHRASING?

02:44.335 --> 02:45.955
COME ON, DAD.

02:45.956 --> 02:48.376
YOU OWN AN ENTIRE FLEET
OF DELIVERY TRUCKS.

02:48.379 --> 02:50.419
WE GOT MONEY.

02:50.421 --> 02:52.591
NO, I GOT MONEY.
YOU'RE BROKE.

02:52.593 --> 02:55.223
ALL RIGHT,
WHAT'S THE NAME OF THIS RAPPER

02:55.216 --> 02:57.216
YOU GOT TO SEE SO BAD?

02:57.218 --> 02:59.598
MC MURDER DEATH,
BUT IT'S NOT WHAT YOU THINK.

02:59.600 --> 03:01.600
WHAT DID I THINK?

03:01.602 --> 03:04.062
YOU KNOW,
THAT HE'S NEGATIVE

03:04.064 --> 03:06.484
AND PREACHES ABOUT VIOLENCE
AND STUFF.

03:06.477 --> 03:08.477
OH, NO,
THAT DIDN'T CROSS MY MIND.

03:08.479 --> 03:11.479
WHEN I HEAR A NAME LIKE
MC MURDER DEATH I THINK,

03:11.482 --> 03:13.272
HERE'S A POSITIVE
YOUNG ROLE MODEL

03:13.274 --> 03:15.124
GIVING BACK
TO THE COMMUNITY.

03:15.115 --> 03:17.365
WHAT'S THE NAME
OF HIS BIG HIT?

03:17.368 --> 03:19.158
"BULLET TO THE BRAIN,"

03:19.159 --> 03:21.449
BUT IT'S NOT
WHAT YOU THINK.

03:21.452 --> 03:23.822
LOOK, SON,
I LIKE RAP MUSIC, TOO.

03:23.824 --> 03:26.834
THE PROBLEM IS --
YOU DON'T GET ANY SHOW FOR $35.

03:26.827 --> 03:29.457
THESE GUYS COME OUT
IN HOODED SWEATSHIRTS

03:29.460 --> 03:31.830
TALKING ABOUT,
"Y'ALL KNOW THE WORDS.

03:31.832 --> 03:34.342
SING ALONG."

03:34.335 --> 03:36.045
MA, HELP ME.

03:36.046 --> 03:38.426
HEY, BOY, YOU KNOW I DON'T LIKE
THAT GANGSTER STUFF.

03:38.429 --> 03:40.049
IT'S DISRESPECTFUL
TO WOMEN.

03:40.050 --> 03:41.430
Michael: THAT'S RIGHT,

03:41.432 --> 03:43.392
BUT I'LL TELL YOU
WHAT YOU CAN DO, SON.

03:43.394 --> 03:45.814
YOU CAN CLEAN UP YOUR ROOM,
YOU CAN PULL UP THOSE PANTS,

03:45.806 --> 03:48.226
AND DECIDE ON WHICH ONE OF THEM
HATS YOU'RE GOING TO WEAR.

03:48.228 --> 03:50.228
WHERE YOU GOING,
MOSQUITO BREASTS?

03:50.230 --> 03:52.610
SHUT UP, DORK.
OH, YOU SMELL LIKE FEET.

03:52.613 --> 03:54.233
OH, YEAH?
YEAH.

03:54.234 --> 03:57.364
Y'ALL KEEP IT UP,
I'LL MAKE YOU KISS ON THE MOUTH.

03:57.358 --> 03:58.738
Both: EW.

03:58.739 --> 04:01.279
GOOD MORNING, CLAIRE.
HOW'S DADDY'S LITTLE...

04:01.282 --> 04:03.282
HEY,
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

04:03.284 --> 04:05.294
WHY I DON'T GET
A GOOD-MORNING KISS?

04:05.286 --> 04:06.666
LEAVE ME ALONE.

04:06.667 --> 04:08.287
LEAVE YOU ALONE?

04:08.289 --> 04:11.289
YOU KNOW I CAN'T START MY DAY
WITHOUT MY KISS.

04:11.292 --> 04:13.292
COME HERE.
GIVE ME MY KISS.

04:13.294 --> 04:14.684
COME HERE. NO.

04:14.675 --> 04:16.675
YOU GOT SPIT ON ME.

04:16.677 --> 04:18.297
BABY, WHAT'S WRONG?

04:18.298 --> 04:20.428
WHAT? SHE JUST NEEDS
A LITTLE SPACE.

04:20.430 --> 04:22.471
ISN'T THAT RIGHT,
SWEETHEART?

04:22.473 --> 04:25.023
LEAVE ME ALONE.

04:25.015 --> 04:27.555
YOU BETTER GO TALK
TO THAT LITTLE HUSSY.

04:27.558 --> 04:31.478
HEY, CLAIRE,
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

04:31.482 --> 04:33.982
NOW, YOU USED TO LOVE IT WHEN
I GAVE YOU A GOOD-MORNING KISS.

04:33.984 --> 04:36.574
THAT'S BEFORE YOU TOOK DOWN
MY D'ANGELO POSTER.

04:36.567 --> 04:38.487
THE MAN WAS NAKED.
AND?

04:38.489 --> 04:41.199
AND HE DIDN'T
HAVE CLOTHES ON.
OH, OKAY.

04:41.201 --> 04:42.661
DID YOU SEE THAT POSTER?

04:42.663 --> 04:45.003
MM-HMM.

04:44.995 --> 04:46.535
I MEAN, UH-HUH.

04:46.537 --> 04:48.537
SEE, EVER SINCE
YOU STARTED WORKING,

04:48.539 --> 04:50.829
SHE'S BECOME
A WHOLE DIFFERENT PERSON.

04:50.831 --> 04:52.621
OH, COME ON, MICHAEL.
SHE'S 12.

04:52.623 --> 04:54.423
SHE'D BE GOING THROUGH
THESE CHANGES

04:54.415 --> 04:56.465
WHETHER I WAS HERE OR NOT.

04:56.467 --> 04:58.837
BUT AT LEAST SHE'D HAVE SOMEBODY
TO BOUNCE THE ESTROGEN OFF OF.

04:58.839 --> 05:01.469
I DON'T UNDERSTAND HER.
YOU KNOW WHAT?

05:01.472 --> 05:03.842
THE OTHER DAY
SHE ASKED ME ABOUT MONISTAT 7.

05:03.844 --> 05:06.854
I THOUGHT IT WAS LIKE
A SINGING GROUP, LIKE TAKE 6.

05:06.847 --> 05:11.267
JAY, I NEED YOU HERE.
I NEED A WIFE, NOT A ROOMMATE.

05:11.271 --> 05:14.271
OH, MAYBE YOU BETTER TELL ME
HOW YOU DEFINE THE WORD "WIFE."

05:14.274 --> 05:16.404
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN TO YOU --
BAREFOOT, PREGNANT?

05:16.397 --> 05:18.397
NO.
YOU COULD WEAR SHOES.

05:18.399 --> 05:21.939
IN FACT, THE RIGHT PUMPS
WILL HELP YOU GET PREGNANT.

05:21.942 --> 05:24.952
I DON'T HAVE TIME FOR THIS.
I HAVE TO RUN. BYE, MICHAEL.

05:24.945 --> 05:26.495
THIS IS SOME
SERIOUS STUFF.

05:26.497 --> 05:29.497
NO, I WANT TO TALK
ABOUT THIS RIGHT NOW.

05:29.500 --> 05:32.120
AS SOON AS YOU
COME BACK HOME,

05:32.122 --> 05:36.262
WE'RE TALKING ABOUT THIS.

05:36.256 --> 05:39.666
HELLO,
EVERYBODY EXCEPT ROSA.

05:39.670 --> 05:41.670
FINALLY, YOU'RE HOME.
ADIóS, MI AMORCITA.

05:41.672 --> 05:44.682
[ SPEAKS SPANISH RAPIDLY ]

05:44.675 --> 05:47.305
YEAH, I UNDERSTAND
WHAT YOU'RE SAYING.

05:47.307 --> 05:49.807
YEAH, YEAH.

05:49.810 --> 05:55.900
YEAH,COMO TE LLAMA
LA BIBLIOTECA,TOO.

05:55.896 --> 05:58.436
BOY, I DON'T THINK
SHE LIKES ME.

05:58.439 --> 05:59.899
Sí, DADDY.

05:59.900 --> 06:02.070
OH, THAT'S CUTE.
SHE'S TEACHING YOU SPANISH?

06:02.072 --> 06:03.112
Sí.

06:03.113 --> 06:05.623
SO WHERE'S YOUR SISTER?
EL BAÑO.

06:05.616 --> 06:08.246
AND WHERE'S YOUR BROTHER?
YO NO Sé.

06:08.248 --> 06:13.038
OKAY,LA CUCARACHA,
LET'S SWITCH BACK TO ENGLISH.

06:13.043 --> 06:14.423
Sí, DADDY.

06:14.415 --> 06:15.495
NO. "YES, DADDY."

06:15.496 --> 06:17.336
OH, YES, DADDY.

06:17.337 --> 06:18.707
ALL RIGHT.

06:18.709 --> 06:23.259
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.
I'M GOING UPSTAIRS.

06:23.263 --> 06:25.643
♪ YOU TRY TO TAKE MY BUCKS,
I LINE THEM UP LIKE DUCKS ♪

06:25.636 --> 06:27.636
♪ PULL OUT MY GAT,
AND I START TO BUCK ♪

06:27.638 --> 06:30.058
♪ 'CAUSE I'M MC MURDER DEATH,
AND I DON'T GIVE A... ♪

06:30.060 --> 06:31.390
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

06:31.391 --> 06:32.721
♪ CLUCK ♪

06:32.723 --> 06:35.733
WHAT DID I TELL YOU ABOUT
LISTENING TO ALL THAT CUSSING?

06:35.726 --> 06:37.516
DAD,
ALL THE MUSIC HAS CURSING.

06:37.518 --> 06:39.518
NO.
MARVIN GAYE DIDN'T CURSE,

06:39.520 --> 06:42.650
EXCEPT MAYBE
WHEN HIS FATHER SHOT HIM.

06:42.653 --> 06:44.663
DAD,
THAT'S OLD PEOPLE MUSIC.

06:44.655 --> 06:47.025
I'M TRYING
TO KEEP IT REAL.

06:47.027 --> 06:49.027
OH, YOU TRYING
TO KEEP IT REAL?

06:49.029 --> 06:52.029
LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING, SON,
WE LIVE OUT IN THE SUBURBS.

06:52.032 --> 06:54.032
THERE'S NO HOOD OUT HERE.

06:54.034 --> 06:56.424
YOU'RE FROM THE MEAN STREETS
OF STAMFORD, CONNECTICUT.

06:56.416 --> 06:58.036
WHERE'S YOUR HOMEWORK?

06:58.038 --> 06:59.338
IT'S FINISHED.

06:59.339 --> 07:00.879
CAN I GET A LOOK-SEE?

07:04.004 --> 07:05.394
HEY, WHAT'S THIS?

07:05.385 --> 07:06.845
WHOA, WHOA.

07:06.847 --> 07:09.257
IS THIS ME?

07:09.259 --> 07:10.469
SORT OF.

07:10.471 --> 07:12.431
IT LOOKS LIKE ME.

07:12.432 --> 07:14.822
GOT THE SAME LITTLE EARS
AND THE FUNNY EYES.

07:14.815 --> 07:17.435
I DIDN'T KNOW THE TOP
OF MY HEAD WAS SO POINTY,

07:17.437 --> 07:19.357
AND WHEN DID I START
GROWING HORNS, SON?

07:19.359 --> 07:20.859
DAD,
IT'S A CARICATURE.

07:20.861 --> 07:23.441
WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT?
THIS IS ACTUALLY PRETTY GOOD.

07:23.443 --> 07:25.453
YOU'RE NOT MAD?

07:25.445 --> 07:27.365
NO.
THIS SHOWS REAL TALENT.

07:27.367 --> 07:30.527
YOU KNOW, YOU MIGHT EVEN WANT
TO RECONSIDER YOUR DREAM.

07:30.531 --> 07:33.491
YOU MEAN FROM WORKING
AT FOOT LOCKER?

07:33.494 --> 07:34.884
YEAH, THAT ONE.

07:34.875 --> 07:37.205
BUT, DAD,

07:37.207 --> 07:39.167
THOSE GUYS GET 15% OFF.

07:39.169 --> 07:41.539
I KNOW,
BUT IF YOU OWN THE STORE,

07:41.542 --> 07:43.502
YOU GET 100% OFF.

07:43.504 --> 07:44.514
FOR REAL?

07:44.505 --> 07:45.585
FOR REAL.

07:45.586 --> 07:47.586
I NEVER THOUGHT OF THAT.

07:47.588 --> 07:49.218
I KNOW.

07:49.219 --> 07:52.139
HEY, THANKS, DAD.
OH, CHECK IT OUT.

07:52.142 --> 07:53.972
WHAT?

07:53.974 --> 07:55.524
MY MUSTACHE
IS COMING IN.

07:55.516 --> 07:59.396
GET OUT OF HERE.
WOW, LOOK AT THAT.

07:59.399 --> 08:01.769
YOU KNOW,
IN A COUPLE OF YEARS,

08:01.772 --> 08:04.402
THAT MIGHT START LOOKING
LIKE SOME REAL HAIR.

08:04.404 --> 08:06.784
DAD, I GOT REAL HAIR
GROWING ALL OVER.

08:06.777 --> 08:08.737
LOOK AT THIS.

08:08.739 --> 08:11.819
UNH-UNH.
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

08:19.419 --> 08:23.079
I CAN'T TAKE THIS ANYMORE.

08:23.083 --> 08:25.473
CLAIRE HAS LOCKED HERSELF
IN THE BATHROOM,

08:25.465 --> 08:27.465
KADY IS
LIVIN' LA VIDA LOCA,

08:27.467 --> 08:33.427
AND JUNIOR WANTS TO SHOW ME
HIS MAN-BUSH.

08:33.433 --> 08:36.443
YES, I GOT THE CLIENT, HONEY,
AND I'M SO HAPPY ABOUT IT.

08:36.436 --> 08:37.726
THANK YOU.

08:37.727 --> 08:39.438
YOU'RE NOT
LISTENING TO ME.

08:39.438 --> 08:41.438
I HEARD EVERY WORD YOU SAID,

08:41.441 --> 08:43.441
BUT I JUST FINISHED
AN 11-HOUR DAY, MICHAEL,

08:43.443 --> 08:44.993
AND WHEN I COME HOME

08:44.985 --> 08:47.985
I WOULD LIKE FOR THE MAN I LOVE
TO SAY HELLO TO ME.

08:47.988 --> 08:49.608
HELLO.

08:49.610 --> 08:51.490
THANK YOU.
THAT'S BETTER.

08:51.491 --> 08:54.661
LOOK, I DON'T MEAN TO SAY
THIS IS YOUR FAULT, JAY,

08:54.655 --> 08:57.205
BUT THIS IS YOUR FAULT.

08:57.207 --> 08:59.577
NO, I'M SERIOUS.
THIS IS NOT MY VISION

08:59.580 --> 09:02.210
OF WHAT A MARRIAGE
IS SUPPOSED TO BE LIKE.

09:02.212 --> 09:04.542
VISION?
AND WHAT VISION IS THAT?

09:04.544 --> 09:06.174
WELL,
LIKE MY MOTHER AND FATHER.

09:06.166 --> 09:08.546
YOUR MOTHER AND FATHER
HATE EACH OTHER.

09:08.548 --> 09:10.548
YEAH,
BUT THEY'RE STILL TOGETHER,

09:10.550 --> 09:12.170
AND YOU KNOW WHY?

09:12.172 --> 09:14.552
BECAUSE THEY HAVE
A SYSTEM THAT WORKS.

09:14.554 --> 09:17.184
SEE, WE DON'T HAVE
A SYSTEM THAT WORKS ANYMORE.

09:17.177 --> 09:18.557
IT BROKE DOWN SOMEWHERE.

09:18.558 --> 09:21.178
NOW IT'S EVERY MAN OR WO-MAN
FOR HIMSELF.

09:21.181 --> 09:24.561
OKAY, SINCE WE'RE
SHARING VISIONS HERE,

09:24.564 --> 09:26.194
I HAD ONE, TOO,

09:26.186 --> 09:29.146
AND IN MY VISION,
I HAD A HUSBAND -- DENZEL --

09:29.149 --> 09:31.149
WHO WAS SUPPORTIVE
OF MY DREAMS.

09:31.151 --> 09:34.451
I AM SUPPORTIVE.
I'M THE ONE THAT PAID

09:34.454 --> 09:36.504
FOR THE FOUR YEARS
OF SCHOOLING, REMEMBER?

09:36.496 --> 09:38.156
WHY?
SO I COULD BE

09:38.158 --> 09:40.618
THE MOST HIGHLY EDUCATED
HOUSEWIFE IN THE WORLD?

09:40.621 --> 09:43.581
YES.
I DON'T UNDERSTAND CALCULUS.

09:43.583 --> 09:46.213
THE KIDS NEED A MOTHER HOME
TO HELP THEM WITH HOMEWORK.

09:46.206 --> 09:48.666
OKAY, AND WHAT DO YOU DO
IN THIS SCENARIO OF YOURS?

09:48.669 --> 09:50.169
I BRING HOME THE BACON.

09:50.170 --> 09:51.550
WELL, HONEY,

09:51.551 --> 09:55.311
I HAVE AN OPPORTUNITY
TO BRING HOME SOME STEAK.

09:55.305 --> 09:57.675
BABY, TODAY MR. ANDERSON
OFFERED ME A JOB

09:57.678 --> 09:59.768
AS A FULL-TIME BROKER.

09:59.770 --> 10:01.100
GET OUT OF HERE.

10:01.101 --> 10:02.721
YEAH!

10:02.723 --> 10:04.143
WHAT DID YOU TELL HIM?

10:04.144 --> 10:07.154
WELL, I TOLD HIM THAT
I HAD TO TALK IT OVER

10:07.147 --> 10:10.397
WITH MY REASONABLE
AND SUPPORTIVE HUSBAND.

10:10.400 --> 10:11.780
WELL, GOOD.

10:11.782 --> 10:14.402
SO YOU TELL HIM
THAT WE TALKED IT OVER...

10:14.404 --> 10:15.624
UH-HUH.

10:15.615 --> 10:18.785
AND MR. REASONABLE
AND MR. SUPPORTIVE SAID NO.

10:18.789 --> 10:21.079
UNH-UNH. MICHAEL,
WE HAVE TO TALK ABOUT THIS.

10:21.081 --> 10:23.831
I DON'T WANT TO TALK ABOUT IT.
WE'LL TALK ABOUT IT LATER.

10:23.834 --> 10:26.594
MICHAEL, I WANT TO TALK
ABOUT THIS RIGHT NOW!

10:26.586 --> 10:30.336
AS SOON AS YOU
COME BACK DOWNSTAIRS.

10:50.901 --> 10:53.151
I'M NOT GOING TO TAKE "NO"
FOR AN ANSWER, MICHAEL.

10:53.153 --> 10:54.783
OH,
I SWEAR TO GOD, JAY,

10:54.775 --> 10:57.235
I DON'T KNOW WHY THIS JOB
IS SO IMPORTANT TO YOU.

10:57.237 --> 10:59.237
WHEN YOU LEFT
YOUR JOB AT U.P.S.

10:59.239 --> 11:01.239
BECAUSE YOU WANTED
YOUR OWN COMPANY,

11:01.241 --> 11:02.621
I SUPPORTED THAT.

11:02.622 --> 11:05.382
NOW I'M JUST ASKING YOU
TO SUPPORT ME.

11:05.375 --> 11:07.585
I KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TRYING TO DO.

11:07.587 --> 11:10.917
YOU'RE TRYING TO TRICK ME
WITH COMMON SENSE.

11:10.921 --> 11:12.341
WELL,
THAT'S NOT GOING TO WORK.

11:12.342 --> 11:15.352
WE CAN'T TALK TO EACH OTHER.
WE NEED A COUNSELOR.

11:15.345 --> 11:16.965
I'M CALLING DR. BOUCHER.

11:16.967 --> 11:19.217
NO, I DON'T WANT
TO GO TO BOUCHER.

11:19.219 --> 11:21.219
THIS WHOLE THERAPY THING
IS A SCAM.

11:21.221 --> 11:22.851
IT'S USED TO LET WOMEN

11:22.853 --> 11:24.863
DO THE TWO THINGS
THEY LOVE MOST --

11:24.855 --> 11:26.265
TALK AND SPEND MONEY.

11:26.266 --> 11:29.016
ARE YOU SAYING YOU DON'T WANT
TO WORK ON THIS MARRIAGE?

11:29.019 --> 11:31.399
JANET, I DO WANT TO WORK
ON THIS -- NO, LISTEN!

11:31.401 --> 11:33.361
I HURT YOU.
I'M SORRY,

11:33.363 --> 11:35.663
BUT THAT WAS
FIVE YEARS AGO.

11:35.655 --> 11:39.405
EVENTUALLY, THEY STOPPED
BEATING RODNEY KING.

11:44.454 --> 11:46.594
MOM?

11:46.586 --> 11:48.206
SHE JUST LEFT.

11:48.208 --> 11:52.248
OKAY.

11:52.252 --> 11:55.262
HOLD ON.

11:55.255 --> 11:58.135
WHAT DO YOU HAVE ON
UNDERNEATH THAT JACKET?

11:58.138 --> 12:00.258
NOTHING.

12:00.260 --> 12:02.220
YEAH,
THAT'S WHAT I'M AFRAID OF.

12:04.184 --> 12:06.194
OPEN IT UP.
LET ME SEE.

12:06.186 --> 12:09.346
OH, NO. YOU ARE NOT
LEAVING MY HOUSE

12:09.349 --> 12:12.559
DRESSED LIKE THAT,
YOUNG LADY.

12:12.562 --> 12:14.442
IT'S JUST
A TUBE TOP, DAD.

12:14.444 --> 12:17.074
NO, IT'S JUST AN INVITATION
FOR LITTLE BOYS

12:17.067 --> 12:19.987
TO SEE YOUR NINNIES.

12:19.990 --> 12:23.240
WELL,
MOM SAID I COULD WEAR IT.

12:23.243 --> 12:25.253
WELL,
WE'LL ASK HER ABOUT THAT

12:25.245 --> 12:28.415
WHEN YOU COME HOME FROM SCHOOL
IN YOUR TURTLENECK.

12:28.418 --> 12:29.788
OH!

12:29.790 --> 12:31.580
PUT ON SOME FLATTER SHOES

12:31.581 --> 12:35.591
AND SOME LONGER PANTS
AND A VEIL.

12:43.223 --> 12:47.603
SHE'S ALWAYS LATE.

12:50.600 --> 12:54.060
IT'S JUST LIKE A WOMAN,
TOO, HUH?

12:54.064 --> 12:56.494
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:56.486 --> 13:00.236
HEY, WHAT DO YOU
KEEP WRITING DOWN?

13:00.240 --> 13:01.700
OH, IT'S NOTHING.

13:01.701 --> 13:05.171
HI. I HOPE YOU HAVEN'T
STARTED WITHOUT ME.

13:05.165 --> 13:07.165
OH, JANET,
THAT WOULD BE LIKE ASKING

13:07.167 --> 13:09.367
THE DAY TO START
WITHOUT THE SUNRISE.

13:09.369 --> 13:11.369
OH, QUIT IT,
DR. BOUCHER.

13:11.371 --> 13:14.371
YEAH,
QUIT IT, DR. BOUCHER.

13:14.374 --> 13:17.094
OKAY,
SO HOW'S THE HAPPY COUPLE?

13:17.087 --> 13:19.257
OH, NOT TOO HAPPY
ABOUT BEING HERE.

13:21.591 --> 13:23.591
MICHAEL HAS ISSUES
ABOUT ME WORKING --

13:23.593 --> 13:26.233
NO. MICHAEL HAS ISSUES
ABOUT YOU WORKING FULL-TIME.

13:26.226 --> 13:28.596
HONEY, COULD YOU PLEASE
LET ME FINISH?

13:28.598 --> 13:30.228
OH,
I'M "HONEY" NOW.

13:30.230 --> 13:32.600
YOU KNOW,
I WAS "JACKASS" LAST NIGHT

13:32.602 --> 13:35.442
WHEN I HAD TO SLEEP
ON THE COUCH.

13:35.435 --> 13:37.435
I DON'T KNOW,
YOU GUYS.

13:37.437 --> 13:39.437
YOU'RE NOT USING
YOUR TOOLS, REMEMBER?

13:39.439 --> 13:42.069
WHENEVER YOU REACH
THIS PART OF THE ARGUMENT,

13:42.072 --> 13:44.072
YOU NEED TO CUT,
REWIND,

13:44.074 --> 13:46.454
GO BACK TO THE TOP
OF THE SCENE,

13:46.446 --> 13:48.446
AND START ALL OVER AGAIN.

13:48.448 --> 13:49.948
[ Makes rewinding noises ]
JACKASS.

13:49.950 --> 13:52.580
JANET, YOU BEGIN.

13:52.582 --> 13:55.172
OKAY, WELL, MICHAEL ASKED ME
TO QUIT MY JOB.

13:55.165 --> 13:56.875
WHAT?
OH, NO, HE DIDN'T.

13:56.877 --> 13:58.337
YES, HE DID.

13:58.338 --> 14:00.168
GIRL, HOW DOES THAT
MAKE YOU FEEL?

14:00.170 --> 14:01.380
OH, YOU KNOW, ANGRY.

14:01.381 --> 14:03.631
HOW ANGRY?
VERY ANGRY.

14:03.633 --> 14:05.433
ANGRY ENOUGH
TO JUST HIT HIM?

14:05.425 --> 14:07.385
LOOK, OPRAH...

14:07.387 --> 14:10.517
YOU SEE -- YOU SEE WHAT
I HAVE TO PUT UP WITH?

14:10.520 --> 14:12.520
EVERYTHING
IS A JOKE TO HIM.

14:12.522 --> 14:15.532
HE HAS A HARD TIME
SAYING WHAT HE REALLY FEELS.

14:15.525 --> 14:17.975
HEY, WHY YOU NEVER
WRITE ANYTHING DOWN

14:17.978 --> 14:20.278
WHEN SHE TALKS?

14:20.280 --> 14:21.940
NOW, JANET,

14:21.942 --> 14:23.982
WHY DON'T YOU ASK MICHAEL
HOW HE FEELS?

14:23.984 --> 14:27.794
MICHAEL,
HOW DO YOU FEEL?

14:27.787 --> 14:31.077
I FEEL LIKE
BUSTING HIS BIG ASS.

14:40.090 --> 14:41.380
[ KNOCKS ON DOOR ]

14:41.381 --> 14:44.261
GO AWAY.

14:44.264 --> 14:47.064
WHAT'S THE MATTER --
YOU HAVE A HEADACHE?

14:48.768 --> 14:51.468
WHAT HAPPENED
TO YOUR EYEBROWS?

14:57.017 --> 15:00.317
I GOT A LITTLE CARRIED AWAY
WITH THE TWEEZERS.

15:00.320 --> 15:02.360
I SEE.

15:02.362 --> 15:03.902
HOW DO I LOOK?

15:03.903 --> 15:08.453
UH, SURPRISED?

15:08.448 --> 15:10.828
I LOOK RIDICULOUS, DAD.

15:10.830 --> 15:13.450
I'M NEVER GOING TO LEAVE
THIS HOUSE AGAIN.

15:13.453 --> 15:16.463
CLAIRE, BABY,

15:16.456 --> 15:19.086
WHY DID YOU DO THIS
TO YOURSELF?

15:19.089 --> 15:22.089
WELL, THERE'S THIS CUTE BOY
AT SCHOOL NAMED J.B.,

15:22.092 --> 15:25.102
AND I WANTED HIM
TO NOTICE ME.

15:25.095 --> 15:29.505
WELL, HE'S CERTAINLY GOING
TO NOTICE YOU NOW.

15:29.509 --> 15:32.139
SEE, I WANTED MY EYEBROWS
TO LOOK REALLY SKINNY,

15:32.142 --> 15:34.812
LIKE JENNIFER LOPEZ,

15:34.814 --> 15:38.064
BUT NOW I LOOK LIKE A THUMB.

15:38.058 --> 15:40.058
WELL,
LOOK ON THE BRIGHT SIDE.

15:40.060 --> 15:42.440
IT'LL BE EASY FOR YOU
TO HITCH A RIDE.

15:42.442 --> 15:45.452
ALL YOU HAVE TO DO
IS LIKE THIS.

15:45.445 --> 15:46.825
THAT'S NOT FUNNY,
DAD.

15:46.826 --> 15:50.446
YOU WANT ME TO HELP YOU
DRAW THEM BACK ON?

15:50.450 --> 15:51.830
WOULD YOU, PLEASE?

15:51.831 --> 15:53.451
SURE. HAVE A SEAT.

15:53.453 --> 15:55.463
CLAIRE,
I GOT TO BE HONEST.

15:55.455 --> 15:56.835
I DON'T REALLY UNDERSTAND

15:56.836 --> 15:59.456
WHAT'S GOING ON WITH YOU
RIGHT NOW.

15:59.459 --> 16:02.669
TO TELL YOU THE TRUTH, DAD,
NEITHER DO I.

16:02.672 --> 16:05.302
ALL I KNOW
IS THERE'S THIS BOY I LIKE,

16:05.295 --> 16:07.925
AND HE'S NOW KISSING
MY BEST FRIEND.

16:07.927 --> 16:10.547
BABY,
FOR THE REST OF YOUR LIFE

16:10.550 --> 16:12.930
THERE ARE GOING TO BE BOYS
ON THIS PLANET,

16:12.932 --> 16:15.942
AND A LOT OF THEM ARE GOING
TO WANT TO KISS YOU.

16:15.935 --> 16:18.805
UNFORTUNATELY, I WON'T
BE ABLE TO KILL THEM ALL.

16:18.808 --> 16:23.268
SOME OF THEM WILL ACTUALLY
SNEAK UNDER THE RADAR.

16:23.273 --> 16:25.113
THAT'S NOT A HAPPY THOUGHT.

16:25.105 --> 16:27.105
OH.

16:27.107 --> 16:31.567
DO YOU REALLY THINK BOYS
ARE GOING TO WANT TO KISS ME?

16:31.571 --> 16:34.951
NOT WITH THOSE EYEBROWS.

16:36.376 --> 16:37.996
BABY, LOOK AT YOU.

16:37.997 --> 16:39.997
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING TO YOURSELF?

16:39.999 --> 16:41.999
YOU'RE CHANGING
WHO YOU ARE.

16:42.001 --> 16:45.551
YOU'RE SHAVING YOUR EYEBROWS,
YOU'RE WEARING TUBE TOPS.

16:45.545 --> 16:48.505
BUT BOYS LIKE WHEN GIRLS
WEAR TUBE TOPS.

16:48.508 --> 16:51.128
FORGET WHAT BOYS LIKE.
WHAT DO YOU LIKE?

16:51.131 --> 16:55.191
DON'T LIVE YOUR LIFE
FOR ANYBODY ELSE.

16:58.398 --> 17:02.398
LISTEN, BOYS LIE.

17:02.402 --> 17:05.021
THEY'LL TELL YOU
ANYTHING IN THE WORLD

17:05.023 --> 17:08.034
TO GET YOU TO DO
WHAT IT IS THEY WANT.

17:08.027 --> 17:10.406
THEY'LL EVEN TELL YOU
THAT THEY LOVE YOU,

17:10.410 --> 17:12.410
BUT THEY DON'T LOVE YOU.

17:12.412 --> 17:14.412
I'M THE ONE
THAT LOVES YOU.

17:14.414 --> 17:17.334
I LOVE YOU, TOO,
DADDY.

17:17.327 --> 17:18.707
I KNOW, BABY.

17:18.708 --> 17:20.328
HEY...

17:20.329 --> 17:21.710
HMM?

17:21.711 --> 17:24.711
YOU GOT YOUR EYEBROW
ON MY SHIRT.

17:24.714 --> 17:30.264
♪ IT'S AFTER MIDNIGHT ♪

17:30.260 --> 17:31.630
♪ AFTER MIDNIGHT ♪

17:31.631 --> 17:34.591
♪ AFTER MIDNIGHT, GIRL ♪

17:34.594 --> 17:36.234
♪ AFTER MIDNIGHT... ♪

17:36.226 --> 17:38.226
HEY.

17:38.228 --> 17:39.978
HEY.

17:39.979 --> 17:42.599
IT SMELLS GOOD.
WHAT YOU COOKING?

17:42.602 --> 17:43.982
[ Jamaican accent ]
CURRIED CATFISH.

17:43.983 --> 17:45.693
[ Jamaican accent ]
MMM, MY FAVORITE.

17:45.685 --> 17:46.985
I KNOW.

17:46.986 --> 17:48.606
IT'S ALMOST FINISHED.

17:48.608 --> 17:50.988
JUST LET ME
PUT THIS STUFF AWAY.

17:50.990 --> 17:54.450
UH-OH. YOU HAD TO GO
TO THE LOVE CHEST.

17:54.454 --> 17:56.464
I MUST BE
IN BIG TROUBLE.

17:56.456 --> 17:58.826
YEAH, THE FIRST TIME
IN FIVE YEARS.

17:58.828 --> 18:01.408
YOU WANT TO SEE
THE THING THAT SAVED YOU?

18:01.411 --> 18:02.621
MM-HMM.

18:02.622 --> 18:04.002
OKAY. LOOK.

18:04.003 --> 18:06.013
OH, THAT'S US
BRINGING JUNIOR HOME

18:06.005 --> 18:07.625
FROM THE HOSPITAL.

18:07.627 --> 18:09.007
YEAH.

18:09.008 --> 18:11.628
LOOK AT ALL THAT HAIR...
ON MY HEAD.

18:11.631 --> 18:14.011
YEAH,
THAT WAS YOUR DR. J. LOOK.

18:14.013 --> 18:16.433
OH, AND, BABY,
REMEMBER THIS?

18:16.426 --> 18:17.596
LOOK.

18:17.597 --> 18:21.347
OH, WHAT IS IT?

18:21.351 --> 18:22.721
IT'S THE STEM

18:22.722 --> 18:24.722
FROM THE CHOCOLATE-COVERED
STRAWBERRY

18:24.724 --> 18:26.734
YOU HID
MY ENGAGEMENT RING IN.

18:26.726 --> 18:28.356
OH.

18:28.358 --> 18:30.728
YOU KNOW WHAT?
IF I CLOSE MY EYES RIGHT NOW,

18:30.730 --> 18:33.070
I CAN ACTUALLY FEEL
THE SAME WAY

18:33.072 --> 18:34.942
I FELT THAT NIGHT.

18:34.944 --> 18:38.204
I'D LIKE TO FEEL
THAT WAY AGAIN, MICHAEL.

18:38.198 --> 18:40.618
JANET, LISTEN, I'VE BEEN
DOING SOME THINKING,

18:40.620 --> 18:42.500
AND YOU'RE RIGHT
ABOUT THE REASON

18:42.502 --> 18:44.502
WHY I QUIT MY JOB
AT U.P.S.

18:44.504 --> 18:46.514
I DID WANT
MY INDEPENDENCE.

18:46.506 --> 18:48.506
YEAH, WELL, I WANT
MY INDEPENDENCE, TOO.

18:48.508 --> 18:51.248
NO, I WANTED INDEPENDENCE
FROM A JOB.

18:51.251 --> 18:53.011
YOU WANT INDEPENDENCE
FROM ME.

18:53.012 --> 18:55.642
NO, I DON'T.
SEE, THAT IS YOUR EGO TALKING.

18:55.635 --> 18:57.635
MICHAEL, YOU THINK EVERYTHING
IS ABOUT YOU.

18:57.637 --> 18:59.557
HEY, LOOK,
LET'S CUT AND REWIND

18:59.559 --> 19:03.389
AND GO BACK TO THE TOP
OF THIS SCENE, OKAY?

19:03.393 --> 19:05.483
[ MAKES REWINDING NOISES ]

19:05.475 --> 19:08.315
LOOK, JAY,
I'VE BEEN THINKING.

19:08.318 --> 19:11.318
I WANT TO APOLOGIZE TO YOU.
I'VE BEEN SELFISH.

19:11.321 --> 19:13.691
I REALLY DO WANT
TO SEE YOU FLY.

19:13.693 --> 19:16.083
I WANT TO SEE
YOUR VISION OF YOU,

19:16.075 --> 19:18.075
BUT THE TRUTH IS,
I'M AFRAID.

19:18.077 --> 19:20.537
OF WHAT, HONEY?
OF TIME.

19:20.540 --> 19:22.540
IT'S ALL GOING BY SO FAST.

19:22.542 --> 19:24.912
I MEAN, LOOK AT JUNIOR.
HE'S ALMOST A GROWN MAN NOW.

19:24.914 --> 19:27.554
I MEAN, SOON WE'RE GOING
TO WAKE UP AND BE OLD,

19:27.547 --> 19:29.547
AND I'LL LOOK LIKE
FREDERICK DOUGLASS,

19:29.549 --> 19:31.549
AND YOU'LL LOOK LIKE
JANE PITTMAN,

19:31.551 --> 19:33.751
AND WE'LL ASK OURSELVES,
"WHERE DID IT ALL GO?"

19:33.753 --> 19:36.393
UM, NO.
I'M GOING TO ASK MYSELF,

19:36.386 --> 19:38.716
"HOW IN THE HELL

19:38.718 --> 19:41.348
DID I END UP
LOOKING LIKE JANE PITTMAN?"

19:41.351 --> 19:45.481
JAY, I ALSO THINK THAT YOU
SHOULD TAKE THAT JOB.

19:48.608 --> 19:50.608
I WANT YOU
TO TAKE THAT JOB,

19:50.610 --> 19:52.940
BUT THERE'S A PART OF ME

19:52.942 --> 19:55.582
THAT'S ALWAYS GOING
TO BE THRILLED FOR YOU,

19:55.575 --> 19:58.695
AND THERE'S ANOTHER PART OF ME
THAT'S GOING TO HATE IT.

19:58.698 --> 20:01.078
WELL, WE'LL JUST LET
THAT PART OF YOU

20:01.080 --> 20:03.580
SLEEP ON THE COUCH.

20:03.583 --> 20:04.743
All: EW!

20:04.744 --> 20:07.594
OH, HOW DO YOU THINK
Y'ALL GOT HERE?

20:07.587 --> 20:08.957
YEAH. SIT DOWN.

20:08.958 --> 20:10.958
OH,
MASHED POTATOES AND PEAS?

20:10.960 --> 20:12.590
EW, GROSS.

20:12.592 --> 20:13.962
Junior: NO, WHAT'S GROSS

20:13.963 --> 20:16.603
IS HAVING TO EAT
MASHED POTATOES AND PEAS

20:16.596 --> 20:18.596
AND LOOKING
AT YOUR EYEBROWS.

20:18.598 --> 20:19.968
HEY!

20:19.969 --> 20:21.599
SHUT UP, STUPID!

20:21.601 --> 20:24.601
[ ALL SHOUTING ]

20:24.604 --> 20:27.614
[ TURNS UP RADIO,
MUSIC PLAYING ]

20:31.230 --> 20:33.230
THIS IS NICE.

20:41.741 --> 20:44.781
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

20:44.784 --> 20:47.674
YOU USED TO LOVE IT WHEN I
GAVE YOU A GOOD-MORNING KISS.

20:47.667 --> 20:50.787
THAT'S BEFORE YOU TOOK DOWN
MY D'ANGELO POSTER.

20:50.790 --> 20:54.210
WHAT DO I HAVE TO DO TO --
WHAT IS MY LINE?

20:54.213 --> 20:56.843
All:
WHAT DO I HAVE TO DO

20:56.836 --> 20:58.836
TO MAKE YOU TAKE MY JOB
MORE SERIOUSLY?
